From {{etyl|sga|ga}} {{term|tar||lang=ga|across, beyond}} < {{proto|Celtic|ter|lang=ga}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|tr|lang=ga}}.  Cognate with Welsh {{term|tra|lang=cy}}; Latin {{term|trans|trans-|lang=la}}, West Germanic *''thurkh'' (English [[through]], Dutch {{term|door|lang=nl}}).  Compare Scottish Gaelic {{l|gd|thar}}.

===Preposition===
